SIMPLE: fighter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fighter
<hw>Fight"er</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧t"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>feohtere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who fights; a
combatant; a warrior.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A boxer; a pugilist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A person with the determination and will to persist
through great difficulty to achieve a goal; one with the courage to
fight and resist an opponent, and to struggle with all one's
powers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A military aircraft designed to
seek out and destroy enemy aircraft; it is usually smaller and more
maneuvarable than aircraft designed specifically for bombing. However,
hybrid <contr>fighter-bomber</contr> aircraft that perform both
functions also are used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fighting</ent>⟦br⟧
